label: Push-Up
description: A push-up is a fundamental calisthenics exercise that targets the chest, shoulders, and triceps. It is performed from a prone position by raising and lowering the body using the arms.

label: Incline Push-Up
description: An incline push-up is a variation of the push-up performed with the hands elevated on a surface, which reduces the weight and makes it easier to perform.

label: Knee Push-Up
description: A knee push-up is a modified version of the push-up, performed with the knees on the ground to reduce the difficulty.

label: Full Push-Up
description: A full push-up is performed with the body in a plank position, lowering and raising the body using the arms.

label: Diamond Push-Up
description: A diamond push-up is a variation of the push-up that targets the triceps more intensely. The hands are placed close together under the chest, forming a diamond shape with the thumbs and index fingers.

label: Clap Push-Up
description: A clap push-up is an explosive variation of the push-up where the hands leave the ground and clap together before returning to the starting position.

label: Pike Push-Up
description: A pike push-up is a push-up variation that emphasizes the shoulders. It is performed with the hips raised high, forming an inverted V shape.

label: Tricep Dips
description: Tricep dips are a bodyweight exercise that targets the triceps, performed on parallel bars by lowering and raising the body using the arms.

label: Pull-Up
description: A pull-up is an upper-body strength exercise that involves pulling oneself up from a dead hang on a bar until the chin is above the bar.

label: Handstand
description: A handstand is the act of supporting the body in a stable, inverted vertical position by balancing on the hands. It requires strength, balance, and coordination.

label: Bar Muscle-Up
description: A bar muscle-up is an advanced strength training exercise that combines a pull-up with a dip. It involves pulling oneself up from a hang on a bar and then pushing the body above the bar until the arms are straight.

label: Chin-Up
description: A chin-up is a variation of the pull-up that targets the biceps more intensely. It is performed with an underhand grip.

label: Wall Handstand
description: A wall handstand is a beginner-friendly variation of the handstand performed against a wall for support.

label: Handstand Push-Up
description: A handstand push-up is an advanced exercise that involves performing a push-up while in a handstand position, targeting the shoulders and triceps.

label: Ring Muscle-Up
description: A ring muscle-up is an advanced calisthenics exercise performed on gymnastics rings, combining a pull-up and a dip.

label: Tuck Front Lever
description: A tuck front lever is a calisthenics exercise that targets the back and core. It involves hanging from a bar and pulling the body into a horizontal position with the knees tucked.

label: Planche
description: A planche is an advanced gymnastic skill that involves holding the body parallel to the ground, supported only by the hands. It requires exceptional strength and balance.

label: Tuck Planche
description: A tuck planche is a progression towards the full planche, performed by holding the body parallel to the ground with the knees tucked to the chest.

label: Full Front Lever
description: A full front lever is an advanced calisthenics skill where the body is held horizontally parallel to the ground while hanging from a bar.
